List the 12 principles of animation.
quash and stretch
anticipation
staging
straight ahead action pose to pose
follow through and overlapping action
slow in and slow out
arc
secondary action
timing
exaggeration
solid drawing
appeal

What makes these 12 principles so important?
All of them combined make the best looking,smoothest,realistic, and appealing
Animation. 

What are four of the principles you will incorporate?
How?
I will incorporate exaggeration by making his head spin when hes in shock,
staging by having very few things happening at the same time and making one
move at a time, timing by having more frames correcly spaced out from each
other for a smother scene, and anticipation by having the snowman winding up
a punch.
